(752, 'Bridge Event:&nbsp;Teaching Math to Young Children Practice Guide: Hands-On Workshop', '', '', '2015-11-16', '2015-11-16', '8:30 a.m.&ndash;4:30 p.m. CT', 'Austin', 'TX', 'American Institutes for Research Austin Office, Conference Center', '', 'This free hands-on workshop explores the evidence-based recommendations in the <em>Teaching Math to Young Children</em> practice guide, produced by the What Works Clearinghouse. The archive materials provide methods for increasing young children&rsquo;s math knowledge, literacy, and competency. Key topics include how to help children use informal methods to represent math concepts, processes, and solutions, and how to engage children in open-ended conversations that build math vocabulary.', '', '', '', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2015-11-16_prekmath2/index.html', 'Early Childhood/PreK, ', '', 'rdrew', '2015-09-24', 'yes', 'yes', 'NM-PK, ', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2015-11-16_prekmath2/index.html', 'no', '', ''),
