(840, 'EWS 101 Webinar: Introduction to the 5 Core Components of Early Warning Systems', '', '', '2016-02-25', '2016-02-25', '10&ndash;11 a.m. PST', 'Webinar', '', '', '', 'Early warning systems (EWS) can identify students at risk of not graduating so that schools can provide support early on to get students back on track to academic success and on-time graduation. In this first webinar of a series, participants will learn about the five key components of an effective EWS:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Building a team</li>\r\n<li>Identifying appropriate indicators</li>\r\n<li>Creating data reports</li>\r\n<li>Mapping interventions to indicators</li>\r\n<li>Evaluating interventions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis is the first in a national series on implementing EWS for dropout prevention from the 10 Regional Educational Laboratories (RELs).&nbsp;<br ><br ><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ews-101-webinar-introduction-to-the-5-core-components-of-early-warning-systems-tickets-21464316348">Register&nbsp;Now</a>', '', '', '', 'https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ews-101-webinar-introduction-to-the-5-core-components-of-early-warning-systems-tickets-21464316348', 'Data Use, ', '', 'jwackwit', '2016-02-17', 'yes', 'yes', 'EE, EL, LA, NM-AG, OK, TX, ', '', 'no', '', ''),
