(970, 'Louisiana Charter Schools Research Alliance Meeting: Addressing Students&rsquo; Needs in Mathematics Through Reformed-Based Instruction', '', '', '2017-03-29', '2017-03-29', '8:15 a.m.&ndash;2:00 p.m.', 'New Orleans', 'LA', 'OPSB Administration Building', '', '<p>This quarterly alliance meeting will center on the major shifts in the Common Core State Standards for Mathematics (CCSSM) for grades 3&ndash;12. We will explore research recommendations for addressing the math achievement gap and for implementing vertical alignment to improve instruction and strategies for narrowing that gap.&nbsp;We will also discuss an alignment matrix tool to identify knowledge gaps related to the alliance research agenda and data sources for addressing them.</p>', 'Darlene Brown', '', 'dmbrown@air.org', '', 'Charter, ', '', 'jwackwit', '2017-03-20', 'yes', 'no', 'LA, ', '', 'no', '', ''),
(971, 'Arkansas Prekindergarten Research Alliance Meeting', '', '', '2017-04-27', '2017-04-27', '9 a.m.&ndash;1 p.m. (MT)', 'Little Rock', 'AR', 'Holiday Inn Airport Conference Center', '', 'Alliance members will receive project updates, including highlights from the Arkansas Prekindergarten Participation and GIS Mapping project, and have an opportunity to network with colleagues. In addition, members will receive training on the use of an alignment matrix tool to identify knowledge gaps related to the alliance research agenda and data sources for addressing those gaps.<br ><br >', 'Janice Keizer', '', 'jkeizer@air.org', '', 'Early Childhood/PreK, ', '', 'jwackwit', '2017-03-20', 'yes', 'no', 'AR, ', '', 'no', '', ''),
