(143, 'REL Southwest Holds Newcomer Workshop in Houston to Explore Resources for Immigrant Students', 'rdrew', '2016-04-25', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_03_08_el_newcomers_news.html', 'REL Southwest Holds Newcomer Workshop in Houston to Explore Resources for Immigrant Students', 'REL Southwest held a timely workshop on the emerging issue of newcomer students, immigrant children recently arrived to the United States, and the special needs and concerns of that population.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_03_08_el_newcomers_news.html', '2016-04-24', 'Read more', 0, 'EL, NM-AG, TX, ', 0, 0, 'yes', 'English learners	', '', '', 'Rachel Drew', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'REL_Southwest_Holds_Newcomer_Workshop_in_Houston_to', '', '', ''),
(145, 'REL Southwest Welcomes New Director and Governing Board Members, Tours Hynes Charter School in New Orleans', 'rdrew', '2016-06-15', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_05_02_springgoverningboard.html', 'News from the REL Southwest Spring Governing Board: Welcome New Members and Director!', 'REL Southwest held its Spring Governing Board meeting in New Orleans on May 24, 2016. Members also toured&nbsp;award-winning Edward Hynes Charter School. Two new members &nbsp;joined the Governing Board: Dr. Kenneth Heydrick and Dr. Brian Riedlinger. We also thanked outgoing REL Southwest director, Vicki Dimock, Ph.D., for her leadership over the past four years and welcomed new director, Michael Vaden-Kiernan, Ph.D.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_05_02_springgoverningboard.html', '2016-06-15', 'Read more', 0, 'LA, ', 0, 0, 'yes', 'Charter schools	Other	', '', '', 'Rachel Drew', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'REL_Southwest_Welcomes_New_Director_and_Governing_Board', '', '', ''),
(146, 'Homer Elementary Wins $50,000 Grand Prize in Collaboration Nation Video Contest', 'jwackwit', '2016-08-04', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_08_04_homer_vidgrandprize.html', 'Homer Elementary Wins $50,000 Grand Prize in Collaboration Nation Video Contest', 'Todd Crabtree, a member of our Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance and superintendent of Byng Public Schools in Ada, Oklahoma, is proud to announce that Byng&rsquo;s Homer Elementary has won the $50,000 grand prize in the Collaboration Nation video contest.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_08_04_homer_vidgrandprize.html', '2016-08-04', 'Read more', 0, 'OK, ', 0, 0, 'yes', 'Rural	', '', '', 'Joni Wackwitz', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Homer_Elementary_Wins_50000_Grand_Prize_in_Collaboration', '', '', ''),
(147, 'West Feliciana Parish Seniors Rank Second in State on ACT', 'jwackwit', '2016-08-05', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_08_05_westfelicianaact.html', 'West Feliciana Parish Seniors Rank Second in State on ACT', 'West Feliciana Parish Schools, whose superintendent serves on REL Southwest&rsquo;s Governing Board and Louisiana Charter Schools Research Alliance, notched Louisiana''s second-highest score on the ACT college admissions test in 2016.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_08_05_westfelicianaact.html', '2016-08-05', 'Read more', 0, 'LA, ', 0, 0, 'yes', 'Charter schools	', '', '', 'Joni Wackwitz', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'West_Feliciana_Parish_Seniors_Rank_Second_in_State', '', '', ''),
(148, 'Archive: Culturally Responsive Resources for Native Students', 'lnail', '2016-10-18', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2016-05-11_crrns/index.html', 'Webinar Archive Posted: Culturally Responsive Resources for Native Students', 'The archive is available for the bridge event "Culturally Responsive Resources for Native Students," co-sponsored on May 11, 2016, by REL Southwest, the Center on Standards and Assessment Implementation, and the National Indian Education Association. The presentation highlighted two online repositories of culturally responsive resources designed to strengthen the teacher-student connection and to support Native American students.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2016-05-11_crrns/index.html', '2016-10-18', 'Access the archive', 0, 'OK, ', 0, 0, 'yes', 'American Indian	Rural	', '', '', 'Leslie Nail', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'archive_culturally_responsive_resources_for_native_students', '', '', ''),
(149, 'More Than 400 Louisiana Charter School Educators Attend REL Southwest Workshop on Student Data Privacy Laws and Culturally Relevant Instruction', 'jwackwit', '2016-11-02', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_04_4-5_larawkshp.html', 'REL Southwest Hosts Louisiana Workshop on Student Data Privacy Laws and Data Use to Guide Culturally Relevant Instruction', 'More than 415 charter school educators in Louisiana attended our two-day workshop in New Orleans on student data privacy laws and culturally relevant instruction.&nbsp;REL Southwest partnered with the Greater New Orleans Collaborative of Charter Schools to host the workshop on August 4&ndash;5, 2016. Participants included teachers and school leaders from more than 10 charter schools as well as data specialists, Louisiana Department of Education (LDOE) staff, and members of REL Southwest''s Louisiana Charter Schools Research Alliance.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2016_04_4-5_larawkshp.html', '2016-11-02', 'Read more', 0, 'LA, ', 0, 0, 'yes', 'Charter schools	Data use	', '', '', 'Joni Wackwitz and Darlene Brown', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'More_Than_400_Louisiana_Charter_School_Educators_Attend', '', '', ''),
(150, 'Archive: Preschool to Kindergarten: Successfully Navigating the Transition', 'lnail', '2016-11-14', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2016-08-02_kinder/index.html', 'Webinar Archive Posted: Preschool to Kindergarten: Successfully Navigating the Transition', 'View the archive for the bridge event webinar "Preschool to Kindergarten: Successfully Navigating the Transition," hosted by REL Southwest on August 2, 2016. The presentation examines research on supporting children''s transition to school and includes a practitioner''s description of her district''s successful kindergarten transition plan.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2016-08-02_kinder/index.html', '2016-11-14', 'Access the archive', 0, 'AR, NM-PK, ', 0, 0, 'yes', 'Early childhood/preK	', '', '', 'Leslie Nail', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Archive_Preschool_to_Kindergarten_Successfully_Navigating_the_Transition', '', '', ''),
(151, 'Webinar Archive: Student Learning Objectives: Lessons Learned and Next Steps', 'lnail', '2017-01-12', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2016-10-19_slos/index.html', 'Webinar Archive: Student Learning Objectives: Lessons Learned and Next Steps', 'The archive is available for the bridge event webinar "Student Learning Objectives: Lessons Learned and Next Steps.&rdquo; The event was cohosted by REL Southwest and the Center on Great Teachers and Leaders on October 19, 2016. Archived resources offer national, state, and district perspectives on the use of student learning objectives in educator evaluation systems.', '', '2017-01-12', 'Access the archive', 0, 'EE, ', 0, 0, 'no', 'Educator effectiveness	', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/newsroom/newsbanner_default.jpg', 'REL Southwest News', 'Leslie Nail', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Webinar_Archive_Student_Learning_Objectives_Lessons_Learned_and', '<p>The use of student learning objectives (SLOs) as one measure of educator effectiveness has become increasingly widespread. With changes in evaluation requirements under the Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA), however, many states and districts are reviewing the role of SLOs in evaluating educators. This free webinar examines SLOs from national, state, and district perspectives to discuss benefits, lessons learned, and next steps.</p>\r\n<p>Click here to view the <a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2016-10-19_slos/index.html">archive of the webinar</a>.</p>', ' ', 'http://bit.ly/2v7pOmm'),
(152, 'REL Southwest and Texas Comprehensive Center Showcase Their Work at the 2017 TASA Midwinter Conference', 'jwackwit', '2017-02-27', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2017-02-16-tasa.html', 'REL Southwest and the Texas Comprehensive Center Showcase Their Work in Texas at the 2017 TASA Midwinter Conference', 'REL Southwest and the Texas Comprehensive Center (TXCC) showcased their work in Texas in a joint session at the 2017 Texas Association of School Administrators (TASA) Midwinter Conference in Austin on January 30. The session&nbsp;highlighted the work that REL Southwest and the TXCC are doing around educator effectiveness, Hispanic STEM outcomes, and English learner education.', '', '2017-02-27', 'Read more', 0, 'TX, ', 0, 0, 'no', 'Educator effectiveness	English learners	STEM	', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa_banner.jpg', '2017 Texas Association of School Administrators (TASA) Midwinter Conference', 'Jackie Burniske', '', '', '', '', '', 'REL Southwest and TXCC Showcase Their Work in Texas', '', '', 'website', 'TASA Midwinter Conference Showcase', 'Learn about the resources we showcased at the 2017 Texas Association of School Administrators Midwinter Conference', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa_banner.jpg', 'Regional Educational Laboratories, Regional Educational Laboratory Program, REL program, REL, Regional Educational Laboratory Southwest, REL Southwest, REL SW, TASA Midwinter Conference, Texas Association of School Administrators, educator effectiveness, Hispanic STEM, English learners, EL, ELL, English language learners, teacher evaluation, educator evaluation, Texas Educator Evaluation and Support System, TEESS, TTESS', 'REL_Southwest_and_Texas_Comprehensive_Center_Showcase_Their_Work', '<p>REL Southwest and the <a class="bold" href="http://texas-cc.org/about_us">Texas Comprehensive Center</a> (TXCC) showcased their work in Texas at a joint session of the 2017 Texas Association of School Administrators (TASA) Midwinter Conference in Austin on January 30. Titled "Evidence-Based Research on Educator Effectiveness and English Learners in Texas," the session drew 52 participants, including principals, assistant superintendents, superintendents, district staff, and education service center staff.</p>\r\n<p>The focus of the interactive session was on the work REL Southwest and the TXCC are doing in Texas around educator effectiveness, Hispanic STEM outcomes, and English learner (EL) education. As related programs within the U.S. Department of Education, REL Southwest and the TXCC are collaborating on much of this work to coordinate efforts and share resources.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 18px;"><a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/about/staff/jason_laturner.html">Jason LaTurner</a>, deputy director of REL Southwest and director of the Texas Comprehensive Center, began the session with an overview of both programs. Three presentations followed.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="yellowbox"><span class="runinhead">Educator effectiveness.</span>&nbsp; <a class="bold" href="http://www.air.org/person/john-spence">John Spence</a>, deputy director of the TXCC, described how REL&nbsp;Southwest and the TXCC are collaborating to promote educator effectiveness in Texas. This&nbsp;work includes projects supporting the Texas Education Agency''s implementation, pilot, and refinement of the state''s new educator evalution system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="dbltriangle2">Learn more about our <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/our_work/inside_project_detail.php?action=view&amp;id=146">educator effectiveness work in Texas</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="yellowbox"><span class="runinhead">Hispanic students'' STEM outcomes.</span>&nbsp; Spence also presented REL Southwest''s report <em>Exploring the Foundations of the Future STEM Workforce: K&ndash;12 Indicators of Postsecondary STEM Success.</em> After receiving a synopsis of the report''s key findings, participants discussed them in small groups using guided questions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="dbltriangle2">View and download the <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/resources/tools_products/reports_guides/4.5/index.html">report and a synopsis of key findings</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="yellowbox3"><span class="runinhead">Academic support for EL students.</span>&nbsp; <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/about/staff/jackie_burniske.html">Jackie Burniske</a>, REL Southwest dissemination director, shared an overview of the <em>Professional Learning Communities (PLC) Facilitator''s Guide</em>. This guide is designed to help teacher teams apply the evidence-based recommendations in the <em>Teaching Academic Content and Literacy to English Learners in Elementary and Middle School</em> practice guide, produced by the What Works Clearinghouse.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="indent">Burniske also featured the <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/resources/tools_products/reports_guides/plc_guide/plc_vids.html">series of 23 videos</a> that accompany the facilitator''s guide. The video series include examples of teachers applying the strategies in the classroom at multiple grade levels. Participants watched a sample video, "<a class="bold" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=caQptEHVRps&amp;feature=youtu.be">Using Graphic Organizers in Writing, 4th&nbsp;Grade Class</a>," and then used the provided video viewing guide to debrief the lesson delivery, including the resources the teacher used, how she engaged students, and the feedback she provided. When asked if their professional learning communities would find the video useful, participants expressed unanimous support.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="dbltriangle2">View and download the <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/resources/tools_products/reports_guides/plc_guide/plc_guide.html"><em>PLC Facilitator''s Guide</em></a> and <a class="bold" href="http://ies.ed.gov/ncee/wwc/PracticeGuide.aspx?sid=19"><em>English Learner Practice Guide</em></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 18px;">All participants received a follow-up email with a full set of the resources shared in the session.</p>\r\n<p>Arlene Longoria, project manager at the Texas Center for Educator Effectiveness, expressed her appreciation. "The session was one of the BEST I attended!" she wrote. "Thank you for the work you are doing for our ELLs."</p>\r\n<p>Longoria also noted that she has shared the <em>PLC Facilitator''s Guide</em> with Pharr-San Juan-Alamo Independent School District and would stay in touch to relay the district''s feedback.</p>\r\n<p class="subhead">About the TASA Midwinter Conference</p>\r\n<p>The <a class="bold" href="http://www.tcpea.org/midwinter">TASA Midwinter Conference</a> is an annual event held in Austin, Texas. The most popular state conference for school leaders, the event provides opportunities for collaboration, learning, and networking. In 2016, the total number of conference participants was 6,500. School leaders from more than 950 Texas school districts, including nearly 800 superintendents, attended as well as staff from all 20 of the state''s regional education service centers.</p>\r\n<h2 class="gallery">Gallery</h2>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa1.jpg" alt="Presenters Jason LaTurner, Jackie Burniske, and John Spence at the TASA Midwinter Conference." ></p>\r\n<p>Presenters Jason LaTurner, Jackie Burniske, and John Spence at the TASA Midwinter Conference.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box push-5">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa2.jpg" alt="Presenters Jackie Burniske and Jason LaTurner prepare to start the conference session" ></p>\r\n<p>Presenters Jackie Burniske and Jason LaTurner prepare to start the conference session.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa3.jpg" alt="7756" width="290" height="240" ></p>\r\n<p>Presenter Jason LaTurner greets session participants as they arrive.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box push-5">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa4.jpg" alt="7759" width="290" height="240" ></p>\r\n<p>Presenter Jason LaTurner provides an overview of the REL&nbsp;Program and REL Southwest.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa5.jpg" alt="7760" width="290" height="240" ></p>\r\n<p>Working in small groups, participants discuss the findings in the report <a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/resources/tools_products/reports_guides/4.5/index.html"><em>Exploring the Foundations of the Future STEM Workforce: K&ndash;12 Indicators of Postsecondary STEM Success</em></a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box push-5">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-02_tasa/tasa6.jpg" alt="7803" width="290" height="240" ></p>\r\n<p>Presenters Jackie Burniske and John Spence listen as participants debrief the classroom instruction shown in a sample video from the <a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/resources/tools_products/reports_guides/plc_guide/plc_guide.html"><em>Professional Learning Communities Facilitator''s Guide</em></a>.</p>\r\n</div>', 'a.bold {\r\n	font-weight: bold;\r\n	}\r\ndiv p {\r\n	line-height: 19px;\r\n	}\r\ndiv p.floater {\r\n	padding: 5px 0px 10px 20px;\r\n	float: right;\r\n	font-size: 10px;\r\n	line-height: 14px;\r\n	text-align: right;\r\n	}\r\ndiv ul {\r\n 	margin-top:0;\r\n 	margin-bottom:0px;\r\n 	padding-bottom: 0;\r\n 	}\r\ndiv li.yellowbox {\r\n    list-styl