(158, 'Spotlight on Services: REL Reference Desk', 'jwackwit', '2017-05-31', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2017-05-askarel/index.html', 'Spotlight on Services: REL Reference Desk', 'Do you wish you had easy access to a reference desk librarian who could answer your research questions about education policies, programs, and practices? You do! REL Southwest provides this support at no charge.', '', '2017-05-31', 'Read more', 0, '', 0, 0, 'no', 'Data use	Other	', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05-askarel/askarel_banner.png', 'Graphic of signpost with arrows labeled: Who? What? Where? When? Why? How?', 'Alana Sutherland', '', '', '', '', '', 'Have an education research question? Ask @RELSouthwest! We provide this service at no charge', 'RELSouthwest, IESResearch', 'pic.twitter.com/NjjYi6O1T6', 'website', 'Spotlight on Services: REL Southwest Reference Desk', 'Do you wish you had easy access to a reference desk librarian who could answer your research questions about education policies, programs, and practices? You do! REL?Southwest provides this support at no charge.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05-askarel/askarel_banner.png', 'Regional Educational Laboratory program, REL program, REL, Regional Educational Laboratory Southwest, REL Southwest, REL SW, Ask A REL, Ask REL Southwest, Ask REL SW, REL reference desk, IES, Institutes of Education Sciences', 'Spotlight_on_Services_REL_Reference_Desk', '<p>Do you wish you had easy access to a reference desk librarian who could answer your research questions about education policies, programs, and practices? You do! Our <a class="bold2" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/ask/">Ask&nbsp;REL&nbsp;Southwest</a> service provides this support to educators at no charge.</p>\r\n<!-- SIDEBAR -->\r\n<div class="sidebar-rt2">\r\n<div class="inline">\r\n<p class="sidebartitle-icon">Archived answers</p>\r\n<img class="icon-rt" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05-askarel/q-a2.png" alt="quotation mark" width="70" height="49" ></div>\r\n<p style="margin-top: -40px;">In 2016, we sent out more than <span class="emphasis">20 responses</span> to questions submitted to our Ask&nbsp;REL&nbsp;Southwest service, and we''re on track to do even more in 2017.</p>\r\n<p>Topics include best practices for preparing aspiring principals, best practices for teaching English learners and newcomers, and the impact of an extended school day.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="dbltriangle-sidebar"><a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/ask/archive.html">View archived answers</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- END SIDEBAR -->\r\n<p>Ask REL Southwest is part of a collaborative <a class="bold2" href="https://ies.ed.gov/ncee/edlabs/askarel/">Ask A REL</a> reference desk service offered through the 10 regional educational laboratories (RELs). This service functions in much the same way as a reference library, providing citations, brief responses, and referrals in response to research-based education questions.</p>\r\n<p>When someone submits a question, a researcher conducts an online search, including databases and websites maintained by federally funded organizations, research institutions, and education agencies. The researcher then compiles a list of relevant peer-reviewed research, which may include policy reports, literature reviews, and publications. Resources are selected on the basis of factors such as date of publication, publisher and funder, and the methodology used to develop the research. When appropriate, the response may also include referrals to other federally funded organizations that may be able to offer assistance. The final response is sent to the requestor by email.</p>\r\n<h2 class="black">How to submit a question</h2>\r\n<p>Do you have a research-based education question you''d like to submit? Here&rsquo;s what to expect:</p>\r\n<ol class="aar">\r\n<li class="aar">\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 12px;">If you reside in Arkansas, New Mexico, Louisiana, Oklahoma, or Texas, submit your question through our <a class="bold2" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/ask/">Ask REL Southwest web form</a> or during an alliance meeting or bridge event.</p>\r\n<p>If you live outside of our region, please visit the <a class="bold2" href="https://ies.ed.gov/ncee/edlabs/askarel/">Ask A REL</a> page on the Regional Educational Laboratory (REL) Program website. Select your region to submit your question.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class="aar">\r\n<p>Researchers will determine whether your question fits within the scope of the Ask A REL service. A researcher may contact you for any needed clarification about your question.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class="aar">\r\n<p>Our reference desk team will conduct a search of common databases and websites and compile a list of relevant resources and referrals. Responses may include electronic copies of federally funded publications or reports, bibliographies and brief descriptions of education research reports and articles, referrals to research projects sponsored by the Institute of Education Sciences (IES), and information about relevant websites and federally funded education organizations.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class="aar">\r\n<p>The response to your research question is drafted and sent to you via email.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="margin-right: 30px; margin-bottom: 20px;">Responses are shared widely and posted on the <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/ask/archive.html">REL Southwest website</a> to make them readily available to the public.</p>\r\n<!-- SIDEBAR -->\r\n<div class="sidebar-full">\r\n<div class="xinline">\r\n<p class="sidebartitle-full">Introducing our reference desk team</p>\r\n<img class="xicon-full" style="float: right; margin-top: -78px;" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05-askarel/askarel_team.png" alt="icon of a group of people" width="70" ></div>\r\n<p>The human effort behind our Ask REL Southwest reference desk service is supplied by <a class="bold" href="http://www.dir-online.com">Decision Information Resources, Inc.</a> (DIR), whose staff works in partnership with REL&nbsp;Southwest. DIR&rsquo;s portfolio of work with the REL Program and the Institute of Education Sciences, which oversees the RELs, includes serving as a member of the REL Peer Review team, providing technical support to REL Southwest, and leading the interim evaluation of the RELs. DIR&rsquo;s technical expertise and familiarity with the REL program makes the organization uniquely qualified to respond to stakeholders&rsquo; education research questions.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0;">DIR has also expanded the Ask REL Southwest service to provide two additional routes for submitting questions: a conversion route and a needs-sensing route. The conversion route enables stakeholders to submit questions at events, such as research alliance meetings and bridge events, or via a member of the REL Southwest Leadership Team. The needs-sensing route draws questions from the research agendas of our <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/research-alliances/">eight research alliances</a> to help address the high-priority education needs they have identified as their focus.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- END SIDEBAR -->', 'a.bold {\r\n	font-weight: bold;\r\n	}\r\na.bold2 {\r\n	font-weight: bold;\r\n	font-size: 13px;\r\n	}\r\ndiv p {\r\n	font-size: 13px;\r\n	line-height: 20px;\r\n	}\r\ndiv p.floater {\r\n	padding: 5px 0px 10px 20px;\r\n	float: right;\r\n	font-size: 10px;\r\n	line-height: 14px;\r\n	text-align: right;\r\n	}\r\ndiv ul {\r\n 	margin-top:0;\r\n 	margin-bottom:0px;\r\n 	padding-bottom: 0;\r\n 	font-size: 13px;\r\n	line-height: 20px;\r\n 	}\r\ndiv ol.aar {\r\n 	margin: 0 0px 12px -10px;\r\n 	padding: 0 0 0 9px;\r\n 	font-size: 13px;\r\n	line-height: 20px;\r\n 	}\r\ndiv ol li.aar {\r\n    font-size: 13px;\r\n    line-height: 20px;\r\n    font-weight: bold;\r\n    }\r\nli > p {\r\n    font-wei