(166, 'REL Southwest Cohosts Bridge Event on Unlocking Key Challenges Facing Arkansas'' Schools', 'blitke', '2017-06-12', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/news/items/2017-05-oeprecap/index.html', 'REL Southwest Cohosts Bridge Event on Unlocking Key Challenges Facing Arkansas'' Schools', 'REL Southwest and the Office for Education Policy at the University of Arkansas cohosted a bridge event titled "Unlocking Key Challenges Facing Arkansas&rsquo; Schools" in Little Rock on September 14, 2016. Presenters focused on three topic strands: early childhood education, rural education, and diverse learners.', '', '2017-05-30', 'Read more', 0, 'AR, ', 0, 0, 'no', 'Early childhood/preK	Rural	', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/aroep3.png', 'Photo of four educators watching a presentation', 'Janice Keizer', 'http://www.air.org/person/janice-keizer', 'Laura Shankland', 'http://www.air.org/person/laura-shankland', '', '', 'REL Southwest cohosts conference on key challenges facing #Arkansas schools #preK #ruraled', 'RELSouthwest, IESResearch', 'pic.twitter.com/37mzV1FD1Y', 'website', 'Unlocking key challenges facing Arkansas'' schools', 'View archived resources from REL Southwest''s bridge event conference addressing issues related to early education, rural education, and diverse learners in Arkansas. Cohosted with the Office for Education Policy at the University of Arkansas.', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/aroep3.png', 'Regional Educational Laboratory program, REL program, REL, Regional Educational Laboratory Southwest, REL Southwest, REL SW, Office for Education Policy at the University of Arkansas, OEP, Arkansas education, early childhood education, ece, prekindergarten, preK, rural education, diverse learners, Arkansas Prekindergarten Research Alliance, ForwARd Arkansas, Center for Research on Children in the United States', 'REL_Southwest_Cohosts_Bridge_Event_on_Unlocking_Key', '<p>REL Southwest and the <a class="bold" href="https://officeforedpolicy.com">Office for Education Policy at the University of Arkansas</a> cohosted a bridge event titled "Unlocking Key Challenges Facing Arkansas&rsquo; Schools" on September 14, 2016. The event was held at the Heifer International Educational Facilities in Little Rock, Arkansas. Presenters focused on three topic strands: <span class="darkgray">early childhood education</span>, <span class="darkgray">rural education</span>, and <span class="darkgray">diverse learners</span>. The event drew 44 participants, including public school administrators, Arkansas policymakers and their representatives, and researchers interested in the topics.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="dbltriangle">View the <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/bridge_events/2016-09-14_aroep/index.html"> archived event resources</a>, including videos, presentations, and transcripts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote class="left-med2"><img class="up-med" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/buttons/quote3.png" alt="quotation mark" >If you can have a high-quality preK program that lasts not just one but two years, you have the very real possibility of generating even more long lasting impacts on children&rsquo;s cognitive development.<br > <cite><strong>&mdash;&thinsp;Dr.&nbsp;William&nbsp;T. Gormley&nbsp;Jr.</strong></cite></blockquote>\r\n<p style="margin-right: 20px;"><span class="darkgray">Janice Keizer</span>, liaison for REL Southwest''s <a class="bold" href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/research-alliances/arkansas_prek.html">Arkansas Prekindergarten Research Alliance</a>, opened the conference with an overview of REL Southwest and its eight research alliances. <span class="darkgray">Cory&nbsp;Biggs</span>, associate director of ForwARd Arkansas, led the opening plenary session, in which he discussed opportunities for systemic change in Arkansas education. <span class="darkgray">Dr.&nbsp;William&nbsp;T. Gormley&nbsp;Jr.</span>, co-director of the Center for Research on Children in the United States, delivered the keynote address, titled &ldquo;Early Childhood Education: Investing in the Future.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>During the afternoon, participants attended breakout sessions on varied topics, including rural teacher recruitment and retention, facilitating a professional learning community to support English learner students, and designing and sustaining accessible prekindergarten programming.</p>\r\n<blockquote class="right-med2"><img class="up-med" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/buttons/quote3.png" alt="quotation mark" >I can''t express how thankful I am that we had&nbsp;sessions focused on rural&nbsp;issues.<br > <cite><strong>&mdash;&thinsp;Bridge event participant</strong></cite></blockquote>\r\n<p>Those who attended shared that what they found most helpful were the &ldquo;explanations of how research connects to current work&rdquo; as well as the chance to engage with "diverse people to discuss education issues.&rdquo; Participants also shared that they gained insights about current issues in early childhood education, in particular the rules and regulations that guide the implementation of high-quality preK in Arkansas.</p>\r\n<h2 class="gallery">Gallery</h2>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box">\r\n<p><a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2080_lg.png"><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2080_sm.png" alt="Janice Keizer, REL Southwest alliance liaison, gives opening remarks." ></a></p>\r\n<p class="caption1">Janice Keizer, REL Southwest alliance liaison, gives opening remarks.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box push-5">\r\n<p><a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2090_lg.png"><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2090_sm.png" alt="Cory Biggs, associate director of ForwARd Arkansas, delivers the plenary session." ></a></p>\r\n<p>Cory Biggs, associate director of ForwARd Arkansas, delivers the plenary session.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box">\r\n<p><a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2106_lg.png"><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2106_sm.png" alt="Participants listen to a session on designing and sustaining accessible preK programming." ></a></p>\r\n<p class="caption1">Participants listen to a session on designing and sustaining accessible preK programming.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box push-5">\r\n<p><a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2102_lg.png"><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2102_sm.png" alt="Dr. Haidee Williams, REL Southwest alliance liaison, presents a session on rural education." ></a></p>\r\n<p class="caption1">Dr. Haidee Williams, REL Southwest alliance liaison, presents a session on rural education.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box">\r\n<p><a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2111_lg.png"><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2111_sm.png" alt="Dr. Sarah Caverly, REL Southwest analytic technical support lead, discusses current issues affecting early childhood education in Arkansas." ></a></p>\r\n<p class="caption1">Dr. Sarah Caverly, REL Southwest analytic technical support lead, discusses current issues affecting early childhood education in Arkansas.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="grid-50 gallery-box push-5">\r\n<p><a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2223_lg.png"><img class="responsive" src="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/photos/2017-05_aroep-recap/2223_sm.png" alt="REL Southwest team members Jackie 