	color: #404040;\r\n 	margin: 30px 0 16px 0;\r\n 	}\r\n.darkgray {\r\n	color: #404040;\r\n	font-weight: bold;\r\n	}\r\nblockquote.right {\r\n	float: right;\r\n	border: 1px solid #ccc;\r\n	background: #f0f0f0;\r\n	width: 175px;\r\n	font-size: 14px;\r\n	line-height: 19px;\r\n	color: #2c6a5b;\r\n	padding: 0px 16px 16px 42px;\r\n	margin: 5px 0px 12px 18px;\r\n	text-indent: -52px;\r\n	}\r\nblockquote.right2 {\r\n	float: right;\r\n	border: 1px solid #ccc;\r\n	background: #f0f0f0;\r\n	width: 175px;\r\n	font-size: 14px;\r\n	line-height: 19px;\r\n	color: #2c6a5b;\r\n	padding: 0px 16px 16px 42px;\r\n	margin: 40px 0px 12px 18px;\r\n	text-indent: -52px;\r\n	}\r\nblockquote.left {\r\n	float: left;\r\n	border: 1px solid #ccc;\r\n	background: #f0f0f0;\r\n	width: 175px;\r\n	font-size: 14px;\r\n	line-height: 19px;\r\n	color: #2c6a5b;\r\n	padding: 0px 16px 16px 42px;\r\n	margin: 5px 18px 12px 0px;\r\n	text-indent: -52px;\r\n	}\r\nblockquote cite {\r\n	display: block;\r\n	font-size: 12px;\r\n	line-height: 13px;\r\n	font-style: normal;\r\n	color: #505050;\r\n	margin-top: 9px;\r\n	text-indent: 0;\r\n	text-align: right;\r\n	}\r\nimg.map {\r\n	float: left;\r\n	padding: 0;\r\n	margin: 0 12px 0 0;\r\n	position: relative;\r\n    top: -4px;\r\n    }\r\nimg.up {\r\n    position: relative;\r\n    top: -10px;\r\n	}\r\nimg.side1 {\r\n    position: relative;\r\n    bottom: -3px;\r\n    right: -3px;\r\n	}\r\n.subhead {\r\n 	font-size: 14px;\r\n 	font-weight: bold;\r\n 	color: #404040;\r\n 	margin: 30px 0 16px 0;\r\n 	}\r\n', 'http://bit.ly/2jgxY33'),
(184, 'REL Southwest Alliance Members Come Together for Final Meetings and Celebrations', 'blitke', '2017-11-28', '', 'REL Southwest Alliance Members Come Together for Final Meetings and Celebrations', 'REL Southwest alliance members held their final meetings of the 2012&ndash;17 contract and celebrated their accomplishments.', '', '2017-11-28', '', 0, 'AR, EE, EL, LA, NM-AG, NM-PK, OK, TX, ', 0, 0, 'no', 'Other	', '/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance2.jpg', 'Alliance members pose for a photo', 'Marguerite Huber', '', '', '', '', '', 'REL Southwest research alliances celebrate their accomplishments over the past 5 years #edresearch @RELSouthwest @IESResearch', 'RELSouthwest, IESResearch', 'pic.twitter.com/TmmpJ4io09', 'Website', 'REL Southwest Alliance Members Come Together for Final Meetings and Celebrations', '', '/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance2.jpg', 'Regional Educational Laboratory program, REL program, REL, Regional Educational Laboratory Southwest, REL Southwest, REL SW, education research, IES, research alliance, researcher-practitioner partnership, collaborative research', 'Alliance_Members_Come_Together_for_Final_Time', '<p>Over the past few months, each of REL Southwest''s <a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/research-alliances/">eight research alliances</a> met for the last time to review and celebrate the work they accomplished during the 2012&ndash;17 contract.&nbsp;The meetings covered a myriad of topics to wrap up the alliances&rsquo; last five years of work together. REL Southwest staff shared published reports for the alliances'' studies, updates on upcoming reports, and best practices for disseminating the results. For example, the Arkansas Prekindergarten Research Alliance held a technical assistance workshop to discuss the results of an alliance project, while the&nbsp;English Learners Research Alliance and New Mexico Achievement Gap Research Alliance devoted time to discussing the role of alliance members in engagement, outreach, and promotion of alliance reports.</p>\r\n<div class="grid-50" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 6px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 5px;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance1.jpg" alt="Photo of four members of the Louisiana Charter School Research Alliance watching a presentation." ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">REL Southwest researchers share the results of a study with the Louisiana Charter Schools Research Alliance</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Some alliances held events. In October, the Louisiana Charter Schools Research Alliance hosted a professional development workshop on new state science standards. Forty-four science teachers attended the two-day event, which was conducted&nbsp;in partnership with the <a href="http://www.gnocollaborative.com/">Greater New Orleans Collaborative of Charter Schools</a>&nbsp;and the <a href="http://www.louisianabelieves.com/">Louisiana Department of Education</a>. That same month, the Texas Hispanic STEM Research Alliance conducted the final workshop of a series aimed at assisting alliance members in incorporating report findings into the <a href="http://www.tstemblueprint.org/">T-STEM (Texas Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics) Blueprint Benchmarks</a>. These benchmarks are used by 124 <a href="http://tea.texas.gov/T-STEM/">T-STEM Academies</a> across the state.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, two alliances spent time looking back on their work. The Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance reflected on how the alliance was formed and the progress members have made over the course of the last five years. The Educator Effectiveness Research Alliance revisited the goals of the alliance and its accomplishments.</p>\r\n<p>Each alliance also provided members with certificates of recognition for their service to REL Southwest over the past five years. The Arkansas Prekindergarten Research Alliance and the Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance gave special recognition to four alliance champions for their exceptional contributions of time and resources, which contributed greatly to the success of each alliance.</p>\r\n<div class="grid-50" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 6px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 5px;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance2.jpg" alt="Photo of members of the Educator Effectiveness Alliance." ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">The Educator Effectiveness Research Alliance gathered one last time to discuss the final alliance research reports and the future of their alliance.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>With REL Southwest''s current contract ending in November 2017, the alliance members discussed what was next for their partnerships. For example, members of the New Mexico Achievement Gap Research Alliance voted unanimously to transition their alliance. Alliance member Doug Rogers, executive director of Dual Language Education of New Mexico, stated, &ldquo;Although the alliance may change in form moving forward, I must say that . . . this [approach] is the way it should be [because] these are our kids and these are our families, so it should be our research. We should also be the ones [investigating] the questions that remain unanswered.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>From 2012 to 2017, the members of REL Southwest''s eight research alliances gave of their time as they worked together to produce and share quality research and technical assistance that served priority education needs in Arkansas, Louisiana, New Mexico, Oklahoma, and Texas. REL Southwest would like to thank all the research alliance members for their commitment and dedication to this important work. We could not have done it without you!</p>\r\n<div class="mobileFullwidth" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 18px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 5px; width: 42%; float: left;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance3.jpg" alt="Photo of members of the Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance." ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">The Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance gathered in October to celebrate the work the alliance has accomplished.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="mobileFullwidth" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 18px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 5px; width: 42%; float: left;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance4.jpg" alt="Photo of members of the English Learners Research Alliance." ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">The English Learners Research Alliance met in October to review the work of the alliance, discuss the study findings, and recognize their members for their contributions to the alliance.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br style="clear: both;" >\r\n<div class="mobileFullwidth" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 5px; width: 42%; float: left;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance5.jpg" alt="Photo of English Learners Research Alliance liaison, Dalia Zabala, presenting David Kauffman with a certificate of appreciation." ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">Dalia Zabala, the English Learners Research Alliance liaison, presents alliance member David Kauffman with a certificate of appreciation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="mobileFullwidth" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 5px; width: 42%; float: left;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance6.jpg" alt="Photo of English Learners Research Alliance liaison, Dalia Zabala, presenting Monica Smith with a certificate of appreciation." ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">Dalia Zabala, the English Learners Research Alliance liaison, presents alliance member Monica Smith with a certificate of appreciation</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br style="clear: both;" >\r\n<div class="mobileFullwidth" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 18px; width: 42%; float: left;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance7.jpg" alt="Photo of Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance liaison, Haidee Williams, presenting Kathren Stehno with a plaque for her service to REL Southwest." ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">Haidee Williams, Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance liaison, presents alliance champion Kathren Stehno with a plaque for her exceptional service to REL Southwest.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="mobileFullwidth" style="background-color: #ebebeb; border: 1px solid #aba7ab; padding: 10px 10px 0px 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 18px; width: 42%; float: left;">\r\n<p><img class="responsive" src="/news/items/2017-11/finalalliance8.jpg" alt="Photo of Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance liaison, Haidee Williams, presenting Sharon Dean with a plaque for her service to REL Southwest" ></p>\r\n<p class="caption">Haidee Williams, Oklahoma Rural Schools Research Alliance liaison, presents alliance champion Sharon Dean with a plaque for her exceptional service to REL Southwest.</p>\r\n</div>', '@media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {\r\n.mobileFullwidth {\r\nwidth:95% !important;\r\n}\r\ndiv p.caption {\r\n   font-size:11px;\r\n   line-height: 18 px;\r\n   margin: 0;\r\n   padding: 6px;\r\n}', 'http://bit.ly/2AILszJ'),
(185, 'Prekindergarten Research in New&nbsp;Mexico: Setting a Research Agenda and Validating an Observation Tool', 'lshankla', '2017-11-28', '', 'Prekindergarten Research in New&nbsp;Mexico: Setting a Research Agenda and Validating an Observation Tool', 'Early childhood education is a top priority for many states. In an effort to address states&rsquo; interests in early childhood education, REL Southwest has two research alliances that study early childhood education questions: one in Arkansas and one in New Mexico. Working with researchers from the REL Southwest, each alliance identified key early childhood topics to study.', '', '2017-11-28', '', 0, 'NM-PK, ', 0, 0, 'no', 'Early childhood/preK	', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/newsroom/PreK-students.png', 'PreK students with teacher', 'Cora Goldston', '', '', '', '', '', 'PreK research in New Mexico: Setting a research agenda and validating an observation tool #edresearch #preK #ece @RELSouthwest @NMPED', 'RELSouthwest, IESResearch', 'pic.twitter.com/adQbq3S83u', 'website', 'Prekindergarten Research in New Mexico: Setting a Research Agenda and Validating an Observation Tool', '', 'http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/common/images/newsroom/PreK-students.png', 'prekindergarten, pre-kindergarten, preK, pre-K, early childhood education, eve, kindergarten, Regional Educational Laboratory program, REL program, REL, Regional Educational Laboratory Southwest, REL Southwest, REL SW, education research, research alliance, collaborative research, researcher-practitioner partnership, KOT, Kindergarten Observation Tool, New Mexico PreK, preK observation, preK evaluation', 'Prekindergarten_Research_in_New_Mexico', '<p>Early childhood education is a top priority for many states. In an effort to address states&rsquo; interests in this area, REL Southwest has two research alliances studying early childhood education questions: one alliance in Arkansas and one in New Mexico. Working with researchers from REL Southwest, each alliance identified key early childhood topics to study.</p>\r\n<p>The <a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/research-alliances/new_mexico_prekindergarten.html">New Mexico Prekindergarten Research Alliance</a> includes stakeholders with a vested interest in early childhood education and includes state agencies, social services organizations, and foundations. Working with REL Southwest researchers, alliance members identified the following topics as especially important and in need of further research:&nbsp; preschool access, programs for special populations, kindergarten readiness, and other topics.</p>\r\n<p>Setting the alliance&rsquo;s <a href="http://relsouthwest.sedl.org/resources/tools_products/research_agendas/relsw_nmprek_agenda508.pdf">research agenda</a> was a collaboration between REL Southwest researchers and alliance stakeholders. Janice Keizer, liaison for the New Mexico Prekindergarten Research Alliance, explains, &ldquo;The very first thing REL Southwest did was to host a meeting where alliance members identified key topics that they were interested in and felt they needed more information, more data.&rdquo; The next step was making these topics actionable &ndash; that is, turning them into research questions that the alliance could study. Says Keizer, &ldquo;Once the research questions were written, the REL Southwest team designed projects around the questions, and then the alliance reviewed the projects. All of our projects spring from the research questions developed by alliance members.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class="subtitle">Validating New Mexico''s Kindergarten Observation Tool</p>\r\n<p>One of the topics that the alliance identified was investigating kindergarten entry assessment tools. Several states are using assessment tools to determine children&rsquo;s knowledge and skills at the beginning of kindergarten as this can help teachers know how to best support individual children at the start of school. New Mexico&rsquo;s Kindergarten Observation Tool (KOT) is one such assessment tool, and the alliance was interested to <a href="https://ies.ed.gov/ncee/edlabs/projects/project.asp?projectID=4531">study the validity</a> of the KOT. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The KOT is an assessment that kindergarten teachers complete at the beginning of the school year. Teachers observe students as they engage in regular classroom activities during the first 30 days of school. Teachers then rate children on twenty-six indicators of children&rsquo;s competency. Teachers can then use the data to individualize instruction, supporting each child in the areas where they still have the most room to grow.</p>\r\n<p>REL Southwest examined the data from the 2015 version of the KOT. Katie Dahlke, principal investigator and principal researcher for REL Southwest, explains, &ldquo;The study examined whether the tool is measuring the areas of knowledge and skill that it&rsquo;s intended to measure, and if not, what areas of knowledge and skill it was measuring.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The study includes psychometric analysis of the KOT items, cognitive interviews with teachers, and inventories of other states&rsquo; kindergarten entry assessments. In addition, REL Southwest analyzed the correlation between the KOT and the Dynamic Indicators of Basic Early Literacy Skills (DIBELS) Next, another assessment of literacy skills.</p>\r\n<p>Alliance members will be able to use the findings to determine appropriate uses of the KOT and to identify opportunities to improve the measure to better support New Mexico kindergarten teachers. REL Southwest&rsquo;s work also reaches beyond the alliance. Based on the methods used in the KOT study, Dahlke presented at the National Principals Conference about the evidence needed to determine if an early grades assessment is valid. Dahlke conducted a similar presentation at the New Mexico Coalition of Education Leaders Conference.</p>\r\n<p>Stakeholders have also validated the 2016 KOT which was administered statewide and also have completed standard setting for the 2016 KOT. Stakeholders are currently investigating the validity of the 2017 version of the KOT. &nbsp;As the New Mexico Public Education Department and the New Mexico Children, Youth, and Families Department continue to refine the KOT, they recognize the importance of testing the validity of new versions. Dahlke notes, &ldquo;This shows New Mexico is committed to having a strong research base for their kindergarten entry assessment and its appropriate uses.&rdquo;</p>', '.subtitle {\r\n	font-size:16px;\r\n	line-height:20px;\r\n	margin-top:20px;\r\n	margin-bottom:9px;\r\n	padding-bottom:0px;\r\n	color:#505050;\r\n	font-weight:bold;\r\n	}	\r\n.subhead {\r\n	font-size:15px;\r\n	line-height:19px;\r\n	margin-top:24px;\r\n	margin-bottom:12px;\r\n	padding-bottom:0px;\r\n	color:#505050;\r\n	font-weight:bold;\r\n	}\r\na.plain {\r\n	text-decoration: none;\r\n	font-weight: 600;\r\n	}\r\ndiv.figure {\r\n	background: #f0f0f0;\r\n	width: 98%;\r\n	border: thin silver solid;\r\n	margin: 22px; 0 18px; 0;\r\n	padding: 0;\r\n	position: relative;\r\n	left: -22px;\r\n	}\r\ndiv.figure p {\r\n	text-align: left;\r\n	font-size: 11px;\r\n	line-height: 15px;\r\n	padding: 1px 8px 8px 8px;\r\n	margin: 0;\r\n	text-indent: 0;\r\n	}\r\nimg.scaled {\r\n	width: 100%;\r\n	padding: 0;\r\n	margin: 0;\r\n	}', 'http://bit.ly/2AGMtIq'),
